  "response_text": "A packed indoor basketball arena fills the screen. A large overhead scoreboard reads “MAKE SOME NOISE…” with “HOME 78,” “VISITOR 80,” and just four seconds on the clock. The stands are crowded, and the atmosphere is tense and expectant. On the court, players in white uniforms and players in blue “STATE” uniforms cluster near the basket. A white-uniformed defender with “DENSEN 25” on his back faces a blue-uniformed player wearing a dark headband. Cheerleaders in green-and-white outfits stand behind them holding shiny silver pom-poms.\n\nThe play continues with the blue team trying to get off a final shot. A blue-uniformed player rises and releases the basketball while white-uniformed defenders jump with arms stretched high. Players on both teams watch the ball arc upward. In the stands, several fans lean forward with open mouths, frozen in suspense: a boy and a woman hold drinks, a heavyset man in a striped shirt stares ahead, a young man in a blue “STATE 1” jersey looks stunned, and a tall man in a bright blue shirt points or gestures toward the court.\n\nThe scoreboard later shows no time remaining, with the score still displayed as 78 to 80, while players begin to spread across the court and the crowd remains fixed on the outcome. The scene then moves away from the arena to a busy public food court or concession area. A red-haired man in a checked shirt stands among people, holding a cell phone to his ear. Beside him is a large decorative hot dog cart with the words “HOT DOGS” on it. He looks upward as if following the game somewhere above him.\n\nFrom behind the same red-haired man, a wall-mounted television is visible high above a counter area. The television shows the basketball game. Large green letters on the wall below spell out parts of a menu, including “DOGS” and other food items. More people stand below, looking upward toward the screen. A higher overhead view reveals a line of customers at a counter, all oriented toward the same general area, suggesting that many people in the food space are watching the end of the game together.\n\nInside a diner-like food stand, a bald man in a white apron stands near a long row of orange drink machines or dispensers. A small television mounted above the dispensers shows the game. Customers at a counter on the left also look toward it. The aproned worker raises his hands near his face in anticipation, caught between working and watching. Back in the arena, a young vendor wearing a blue apron and carrying a tray of pink drink cartons watches from the aisle, his face lifted toward the court. Small white legal text appears along the bottom of the screen during this part, including a coverage disclaimer that is only partly legible.\n\nThe commercial briefly shows people gathered outside a storefront at night, looking through large windows at multiple televisions inside. One man in the group holds a phone to his ear. The same small disclaimer text continues along the bottom. A closer view through the glass shows several adults standing outside, faces tilted up toward the screens inside, with city lights reflected in the window.\n\nBack in the arena, a group of young pep-band members in matching blue “STATE” shirts sit among red seats with drums, a trombone, and cymbals. A drummer holds sticks above a drum and watches intently. The court reappears, with players still gathered under the high arena lights. Then a close view of the hoop shows the white net hanging from a red rim above the red baseline area, with cheerleaders lined up behind the backboard.\n\nThe vendor in the blue apron is shown again, now shouting or cheering, clutching his tray of drinks with one hand and making a fist with the other. The players and crowd erupt. A blue-uniformed player wearing a headband throws both arms up, mouth wide open in celebration. The scene cuts back to the diner, where the aproned worker and customers raise their arms in celebration while the television remains visible ab